classDiagram
    %% PawPal+ final UML (Phase 6) - matches pawpal_system.py

    class Task {
        +str title
        +str category
        +str time
        +int duration_minutes
        +str priority
        +str frequency
        +bool completed
        +str date
        +mark_complete() None
        +next_occurrence() Task | None
    }

    class Pet {
        +str name
        +str species
        +str breed
        +list~str~ medications
        +list~Task~ tasks
        +add_task(task) None
        +task_count() int
    }

    class Owner {
        +str name
        +list~Pet~ pets
        +add_pet(pet) None
        +get_pet(name) Pet | None
        +all_tasks() list~tuple~
    }

    class Scheduler {
        +Owner owner
        +get_today_schedule() list~tuple~
        +sort_by_time(pet_tasks) list~tuple~
        +filter_tasks(pet_tasks, pet_name, completed) list~tuple~
        +detect_conflicts(pet_tasks) list~str~
        +mark_task_complete(pet, task) Task | None
    }

    Owner "1" --> "*" Pet : owns
    Pet "1" --> "*" Task : has
    Scheduler "1" --> "1" Owner : reads live via all_tasks()

    note for Scheduler "Holds a reference to Owner, not a copy.\nAlways reads owner.all_tasks() so it\nnever goes stale after pets/tasks are added."
    note for Task "next_occurrence() returns None unless\nfrequency is 'daily' or 'weekly'.\nUsed by Scheduler.mark_task_complete()\nto auto-schedule recurring tasks."
